Reflecting on the course as a whole, I believe my strongest growth came from learning how to revise with certain intention rather than impulse. Across multiple writing tasks, I moved away from the instinct to add more explanation and instead focused on refining tone, removing excess, and allowing meaning to emerge through structure, silence, and mainly implication. Drawing inspiration helped me understand how loss can be conveyed quietly and with dignity, not through spectacle but through absence and inevitability. This perspective reshaped how I approached not only Remembrance, but all of my creative and analytical work throughout the course, particularly in how I handled themes of displacement, memory, and cultural erasure.

Overall, this course helped me develop confidence in writing with restraint and purpose. I learned that powerful storytelling does not depend on dramatic events or explicit commentary, but on careful attention to what disappears, what is forgotten, and what remains unspoken. These lessons will continue to influence how I read, analyze, and create narratives.`,
